Doing so makes it easier to build long-range dependencies. Multi-headed attention allows attending different aspects,
such as linguistic information, voice color and prosody. With guided cross-attention (next section), however, we found that MHA takes longer to compute than weâ€™d like. We therefore opt for single-headed cross-attention between encoder and decoder.
